{% extends "base.html.j2" %}

{% block head %}
<title>Glossary</title>
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div id="container">
  <div id="main-heading">
    <h1>Glossary</h1>
  </div>
  <div id="measurements">
    <div class="heading">
      <h2>Measurements</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>Culmen length</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>The culmen is the upper part of a penguin's bill, with the length
        measured from the tip of the bill upwards to a set point.</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>Culmen depth</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>The culmen depth is measured from the top part of the bill to the 
        bottom part of the bill.</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>δ13C</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>The ratio of the 2 stable carbon isotopes 13C:12C; tells us about 
        foraging behaviour, such as inshore vs. offshore foraging 
        <a href=https://www.int-res.com/articles/meps2002/234/m234p289.pdf>
        (Forero et al., 2002, p.290)</a>.
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>δ15N</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>The ratio of the 2 stable nitrogen isotopes 15N:14N; tells us the 
        trophic level, or position of an organism in the food chain 
        <a href=http://people.uncw.edu/emslies/documents/vasiletal.2012-rcms.pdf>
        (Vasil et al., 2012, p.487)</a>.
      </h4>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div id="statistics">
    <div class="heading">
      <h2>Statistics</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>Linear regression</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>Can some of the variation in a variable be 'explained' by taking 
        another variable into account? i.e. is there a correlation between the 
        two variables? <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nk2CQITm_eo">
        (StatQuest with Josh Starmer, 2017)</a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <h3>Multiple regression</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
      <h4>Can some of the variation in a variable be 'explained' by taking two 
        other variables into account? i.e. is there a correlation between the 
        three variables that's stronger than just the two on their own? 
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zITIFTsivN8">
        (StatQuest with Josh Starmer, 2017)</a>
      </h4>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
